,"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/gl13es","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/gl13es/john_regehr_s_integers_c_quiz"},{"short_id":"r87zln","created_at":"2026-05-21T10:09:32.000-05:00","title":"Internships for early university / no former employment","url":"","score":19,"flags":0,"comment_count":10,"description":"\u003cp\u003eAs a rising freshman beginning an undergraduate computer science degree this fall, I wonder what internship opportunities (FOSS preferred) are there, for applicants in early university or who otherwise have no former employment experience (despite, perhaps, contributions to FOSS).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePossible template, adapted from previous \u003ccode\u003et/job\u003c/code\u003e posts:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e**Company:** XYZ\r\n\r\n**Company website:** WWW\r\n\r\n**Position(s):** ABC\r\n\r\n**Target applicant pool:** XXX (for example, \"graduating in 2030\", \"any undergraduate pursuing a degree in CS/etc\", etc.)\r\n\r\n**Duration:** XXX\r\n\r\n**Location:** XXX (please include whether REMOTE worldwide/US/EU/etc or ONSITE)\r\n\r\n**Description:** XYZ\r\n\r\n**Tech stack:** ABC\r\n\r\n**Compensation:** XXX\r\n\r\n**Contacts:** WWW\r\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI think comments other than listings (e.g., advice and such) should also be welcome here!\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"As a rising freshman beginning an undergraduate computer science degree this fall, I wonder what internship opportunities (FOSS preferred) are there, for applicants in early university or who otherwise have no former employment experience (despite, perhaps, contributions to FOSS).\r\n\r\nPossible template, adapted from previous `t/job` posts:\r\n\r\n```\r\n**Company:** XYZ\r\n\r\n**Company website:** WWW\r\n\r\n**Position(s):** ABC\r\n\r\n**Target applicant pool:** XXX (for example, \"graduating in 2030\", \"any undergraduate pursuing a degree in CS/etc\", etc.)\r\n\r\n**Duration:** XXX\r\n\r\n**Location:** XXX (please include whether REMOTE worldwide/US/EU/etc or ONSITE)\r\n\r\n**Description:** XYZ\r\n\r\n**Tech stack:** ABC\r\n\r\n**Compensation:** XXX\r\n\r\n**Contacts:** WWW\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think comments other than listings (e.g., advice and such) should also be welcome here!","submitter_user":"runxiyu","user_is_author":true,"tags":["ask","job"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/r87zln","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/r87zln/internships_for_early_university_no"},{"short_id":"ofd0cf","created_at":"2026-05-21T10:00:09.000-05:00","title":"KotlinConf’26 Keynote Highlights: Advances in Language Design, Tooling, AI-Driven Workflows, and Multiplatform Development | The Kotlin Blog","url":"https://blog.jetbrains.com/kotlin/2026/05/kotlinconf26-keynote-highlights/","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"snej","user_is_author":false,"tags":["kotlin"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ofd0cf","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ofd0cf/kotlinconf_26_keynote_highlights"},{"short_id":"aezmj2","created_at":"2026-05-21T09:04:37.000-05:00","title":"L1 instruction cache set conflicts, associativity, and code alignment in Go","url":"https://blog.andr2i.com/posts/2026-05-19-a-regression-in-code-i-didn-t-touch.html","score":4,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"jmillikin","user_is_author":false,"tags":["go","performance"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/aezmj2","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/aezmj2/l1_instruction_cache_set_conflicts"},{"short_id":"yy3xax","created_at":"2026-05-21T08:42:03.000-05:00","title":"FatGid - FreeBSD 14.x kernel LPE","url":"https://fatgid.io/","score":6,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"fro","user_is_author":false,"tags":["freebsd","security"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/yy3xax","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/yy3xax/fatgid_freebsd_14_x_kernel_lpe"},{"short_id":"ulkriy","created